<div style="width:600px;margin: 0 auto;padding-top:30px;">

<%= form_for(resource, :as => resource_name, :url => registration_path(resource_name)) do |f| %>
  <%= devise_error_messages! %>

  <p>Welcome to <em>Ridings</em>, a game simulating the life and soul of Canadian politics. Now, only a few minutes separate you from the path to total power!</p><br />
  
  <p>Enter your <strong>e-mail address.</strong> This will be used to log into the site.</p>
  <p><%= f.email_field :email %></p>
  
  <p>Create a <strong>password</strong> for your account, type it twice for confirmation.</p>
  <p><%= f.password_field :password, 'placeholder' => 'Password Once' %>
  <%= f.password_field :password_confirmation, 'placeholder' => 'Password Twice' %></p>
  
  <p>OK, you're done with the boring account stuff. Now let's start with your <em>in-game character</em>. Invent a realistic-sounding <strong>first and last name</strong> for your character (doesn't have to be your real name). <p><em>Hint: Canada is a multicultural society, so any wordly name would be fine. Just try not to steal a famous person's full name. </em></p></p>
 <p> <%= f.text_field :first_name, 'placeholder' => 'First Name' %> <%= f.text_field :last_name, 'placeholder' => 'Last Name' %></p>

  <p><%= f.submit "Next Step" %></p>
<% end %>



